description:
Breakfast Special

Sociopolitical Documentary hosted by Rick Sebak, published by PBS in 2010 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

A celebration of great morning meals across America. Oh, bacon and eggs! Corned beef hash! Buckwheat pancakes! This BREAKFAST SPECIAL is a celebration of going out for breakfast! It's risotto in Ohio, Scotch eggs in Oregon, congee or &quot;jook&quot; in San Francisco, and breakfast with a Cuban touch in Florida. It's grits and gumbo in Georgia and a place to take your pooch in Portland. This documentary is part travelogue, part food show, part portrait of America as explained and enjoyed by people who get up early and find good food. Warning: This program may make you hungry and inspire you to go out for breakfast. 60 minutes Special features: A making-of video: &quot;Cooking Up A Breakfast Special!&quot; with more beautiful breakfasts! And unseen footage from other places with great morning meals!

